<p>Fátima Bosch Fernández of Mexico was crowned Miss Universe 2025 in Thailand on Friday, concluding a headline-grabbing pageant season in Bangkok [bbc.com#1][nytimes.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][euronews.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1]. Her victory followed weeks of controversy after she briefly walked out during a live-streamed event in protest of a sharp scolding by a local organizer; the episode sparked solidarity, a public apology and further turbulence around the event [npr.org#1][pbs.org#1][bbc.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. Bosch became the fourth Mexican woman to win the title [abs-cbn.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/a9lQgjsqf51zRuejkFmkwPC0opSOXje5OqNWqfHDtomyZrRM_BFo28y-f8ACNQQt2Le_JPivbodWbxsxz7FpqVYumHx1CK9KB00XpA8Df0ZZsTk7LmjeJnt9vn20c02mqS2weX7To6k8R1iA8oCRCvJlG7Hwk1b3HDBKZeQJSnAb67csBI_dFOZSTRVVYrR0grBxNg' alt='Mexico&#x27;s Fátima Bosch was named Miss Universe on Friday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Protest and apology: Bosch’s walkout in response to a public scolding by a local organizer drew support and was followed by a tearful public apology from the organizer [pbs.org#1][washingtonpost.com#1][npr.org#1]</li><li>Rigging allegations: A former judge alleged rigging during the competition, and reports noted judges quitting amid the uproar [npr.org#1][thehindu.com#1]</li><li>Country milestone: Her win makes Bosch the fourth Mexican to hold the Miss Universe crown [abs-cbn.com#1]</li><li>Regional placements: The Philippines’ Ahtisa Manalo finished as third runner-up at the Thailand finale [abs-cbn.com#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Fátima Bosch Fernández (Miss Mexico): She walked out after being sharply scolded during a live-streamed event, then returned to compete and ultimately won the crown [washingtonpost.com#1][bbc.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/style/2025/11/21/mexico-fatima-bosch-miss-universe-winner/'>Washington Post, BBC</a>)</li><li>Local pageant organizer: Issued a public, tearful apology following the incident [pbs.org#1][washingtonpost.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/mexico-contestant-claims-miss-universe-crown-after-standing-up-to-pageant-bullying'>PBS NewsHour, Washington Post</a>)</li><li>Former judge: Alleged the competition was rigged, adding to scrutiny of the event [npr.org#1]. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/11/21/nx-s1-5616219/miss-universe-mexico-scandals'>NPR</a>)</li><li>Fellow contestants and supporters: Displayed solidarity around the bullying controversy as the pageant moved toward the final show [pbs.org#1][bbc.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cgmxmxljg8mo'>PBS NewsHour, BBC</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/11/21/nx-s1-5616219/miss-universe-mexico-scandals'>A new Miss Universe is crowned, weeks after she left a pageant event in protest</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/miss-mexico-wins-miss-universe-contest-after-host-insult-drama'>Miss Mexico wins Miss Universe contest after host insult drama</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/video/2025/11/21/miss-universe-mexicos-fatima-bosch-who-stood-up-to-organisers-crowned-2025-winner'>Miss Universe: Mexico’s Fatima Bosch, who stood up to organisers, crowned 2025 winner</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/miss-mexico-fatima-bosch-wins-miss-universe-contest-after-host-insult-drama/article70306346.ece'>Miss Mexico Fatima Bosch wins Miss Universe contest after host insult drama</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/lifestyle/fatima-bosch-miss-universe-2025-fatima-bosch-mexico-miss-universe-2025-winner-why-fatima-bosch-won-miss-universe-2025-results-fatima-bosch-performance-miss-universe-miss-universe-2025-mexico-win-fatim-13952684.html'>5 things that made Mexico&#x27;s Fatima Bosch win the Miss Universe 2025 pageant</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newsh